doc.previous: On 20 February 2013, Ilyushin Finance Company converted the letter of intent it signed in August 2011 into a purchase agreement, subject to approval by its shareholders, for 32 CS300 aircraft.[62] On the same day, Pratt & Whitney's PW1500G was granted certification by Transport Canada.[63] The PW1500G powers the CSeries.
doc.after: An extensive update on the CSeries program was presented on 7 March 2013; the first "flight test vehicle" (FTV) was displayed in an almost completed state, along with three other FTVs in various states of assembly.[64][65] The 160-seat "Extra Capacity" version of the CS300, featuring two sets of over wing emergency exits, was also presented.[64]
